Create Your Amazon Connect Contact Center

Set up your contact center for Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect. When you create a contact center in Voice, Salesforce creates an Amazon Connect instance and two Salesforce connected apps.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To view the Amazon Contact Centers page:	Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers
To create and manage a contact center:	Contact Center Admin

Before starting this task, assign the Contact Center Admin permission set to at least one user and find out where your contact center is physically located.

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Amazon Setup, then select Amazon Setup.
In the Set Up Your Contact Center section, click Create Contact Center. The Create Contact Center wizard opens.

Enter a display name for your contact center.
Enter an internal name for your contact center. The internal name must be unique to your org, contain fewer than 20 characters, start with a letter, and contain only alphanumeric characters.

Select the region thatâ€™s closest to where your contact center is located geographically.
Click Next.
Select at least one administrator for the contact center.
Click Done. The window closes. It can take a few minutes to create the contact center.

When you create the contact center, Salesforce creates these objects:

Default for Voice routing configuration.
SCV Basic Queue queue.
Single Sign-On Connected App and REST API OAuth Connected App.

After creating your contact center, configure it by adding agents, setting up phone channels, and setting up workspaces.
title: Setting Up Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect
